channel.title: I wanna give feedback for your songs!
channel.description: I know that Alyen made his “I wanna hear your music” thread but I feel like sometimes specific feedback is really needed. This thread is for single sons only. Please don’t spam it with a constant barrage of your songs. I have created this to allow serious legitimate feedback. Please no joking or memes in this thread. I also enjoy a joke but this is not the place. If your songs sucks I’m in a say it sucks. If it’s aweosme I’m gonna say ids awesome. If I hate he overuse of sweepers I’m gonna say it. Please note most feedback is my opinion so it is not necessarily shared by all. If you want to know yet inspired me to do this it is that I followe the tracks and collabs category but it was overwhelming since it wasn’t a list. If you feel you must explain the song do so along with the link but the post is preferred to be just a link. Once again, do not get offended if I say I don’t like your song, I’m trying to give honest feedback. Also please no multi-projects (albums, els, etc.) as they will be skipped. I hope this turns into something productive and helpful for the community and I can make a difference through it. Thanks :)

item.title: I wanna give feedback for your songs!
item.dc:creator: MisterMaster
item.description:
We’ve had a few threads posted this week, with people offering to review tracks. At first there was just one thread, then two and now others are copying the idea.

If anyone wants to provide feedback on a track, the best way to do it is by responding to threads in the #tracks category. We all know that anyone who posts a song in the tracks category wants your feedback, so we don’t need a new seperate thread for each individual reviewer.

This thread is being closed now, to stop others from copying it.

item.title: I wanna give feedback for your songs!
item.dc:creator: Trey
item.description:
Overall, I liked the track! Very chill and smooth kind of feel. Just a few things I noticed.

At 0:23 the kick came in a little too strong as well as the claps and symbol. maybe a little volume and/or low pass automation would be nice to kind of bring them in smoother. That goes for each time they happen.
Maybe later in the song you could try and change up the melody a little, just to spice it up and also maybe condense one or two scenes because there were some parts that were kind of repetitive imo. Good song!

item.title: I wanna give feedback for your songs!
item.dc:creator: therealejoc
item.description:
Okay so first off. I like this track a lot. But you already knew that. I suppose things you could do to make it better… hmmm. I suppose adding drum varieties would be cool. Especially at the beginning the drums are kinda simple. This isn’t necessarily bad but if you add some minute, almost unnoticeable details it can really spice up the track. The second half is my favorite part though. It actually reminds me a lot of my own music, which is probably why I like it so much. I would love to do a remix of this and see if I could take it a slightly different direction while keeping the overall vibe.
